<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-06T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="721" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d721">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.516/380: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-06T12:00:00-05:00">July 6,
                                1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>56. My telegram of July 5, 1 p.m.<note n="27" xml:id="d721fn27">Not
                                printed.</note> From de la Rue.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“Bank officials here have just received word that Council for Foreign
                                55 [<hi rend="italic">sic</hi>] Bondholders has not submitted panel
                                and will not meet until next week.</p>
                            <p>All arrangements made here for transfer Monday, July 8. Do you
                                perceive any objection to our going ahead as planned?”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chapin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>